      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Minor] Line 74: computeCongestionScore() divides by configurable scale values without validating them. If a caller supplies congestionLossScale or congestionRttScale as 0, this produces infinities/NaNs and can make bitrate decisions unpredictable. Clamp or reject invalid config values in the constructor/setter path before use.\n```suggestion\n    const auto lossScale \u003d std::max(cfg_.congestionLossScale, 0.001f);\n    const auto rttScale \u003d std::max(cfg_.congestionRttScale, 0.001f);\n    float lossComponent \u003d std::max(0.0f, (ewmaLoss_ - cfg_.baselineLoss) / lossScale);\n    float rttExcess \u003d (baselineRtt_ \u003e 0) ? std::max(0.0f, ewmaRtt_ - baselineRtt_) : ewmaRtt_;\n    float rttComponent \u003d rttExcess / rttScale;\n```",
      "revId": "5597f66cc7a60003d0c0a64d92a941072d897385",
