      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T10:12:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 198: bwController_.reset() resets the controller target to the default 800 Kbps, but bwControllerInitialized_ remains true after the first setupVideoBitrateInfo() call. On later sender restarts or call restarts, setupVideoBitrateInfo() will only update limits and will not reseed the controller with the negotiated/current codec bitrate, so the next RTCP update can force video back toward 800 Kbps regardless of codec settings. Reset the initialization flag whenever the controller is reset, or explicitly seed from the current codec bitrate after reset.\n```suggestion\n        bwController_.reset();\n        bwControllerInitialized_ \u003d false;\n```",
      "revId": "5597f66cc7a60003d0c0a64d92a941072d897385",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
