      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T10:12:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 657: The RR-loss path removed the previous restart and invalid-jitter guards, so stale RTCP reports right after encoder restart or pathological jitter values can now drive the new controller and unnecessarily reduce bitrate. This regresses the old protection in dropProcessing(). Restore those filters before calling bwController_.update().\n```suggestion\n    RTCPInfo rtcpi {};\n    if (check_RCTP_Info_RR(rtcpi)) {\n        auto now \u003d clock::now();\n        auto restartTimer \u003d now - lastMediaRestart_;\n        if (restartTimer \u003c DELAY_AFTER_RESTART + std::chrono::seconds(1))\n            return;\n#ifndef __ANDROID__\n        if (rtcpi.jitter \u003e 1000)\n            return;\n#endif\n        auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.update(rtcpi.packetLoss, static_cast\u003cfloat\u003e(rtcpi.jitter), rtcpi.latency);\n        setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n    }\n```",
